<Layout title="Emergency Resources" description="If you are in crisis or experiencing an emergency, seek immediate help.">
  <h1>Emergency & Crisis Resources</h1>
  <p>If you are in immediate danger or experiencing a mental health emergency, call your local emergency number (e.g., 911 in the U.S.) or a crisis hotline.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>United States:</strong> 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline</li>
    <li><strong>Canada:</strong> Talk Suicide Canada (1-833-456-4566)</li>
    <li><strong>UK & Ireland:</strong> Samaritans (116 123)</li>
    <li><strong>Australia:</strong> Lifeline (13 11 14)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>These resources are external and not affiliated with this practice.</p>
</Layout>
